    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.PageTitle">Mouse Angle Calibration</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Instructions.Title">How To Use</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Instructions.Step1">1. Click the measurement field below to start and lock the cursor.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Instructions.Step2">2. Swipe left and right naturally at least 30 times while keeping what you consider level.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Instructions.Step3">3. Right click pauses the session so you can inspect the recommended angle; click the field again to continue the same session.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Instructions.Step4">4. Repeat after adjusting grip or pad angle until the recommendation stays within your preferred range.</sys:String>
