    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.AwaitingInput">Locked and waiting for the first movement from any mouse to begin measuring. Right click pauses.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.Measuring">Measuring: move the current measurement mouse left and right at least 30 times. Right click pauses.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.Paused">Paused: click the measurement field again, then move any mouse to resume.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.ResultReady.Active">The recommended angle is ready. Keep swiping the current measurement mouse for better accuracy; right click pauses.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.ResultReady.Paused">The recommended angle is ready. Click the measurement field again, then move any mouse to resume.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.NoDevice">No mouse is currently available, so angle calibration cannot start.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Hint.DeviceDisconnected">The current measurement mouse was disconnected. Click the field again and move any mouse to start a new pass.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.InsufficientProgress">The trace is still building up. Keep swiping a bit longer for a steadier result.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.Imbalance">Left and right passes are uneven. Try to keep both sides more symmetrical.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.HighDispersion">The trace is spreading too much. Try to keep the path straighter and steadier.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.Outliers">Too many outlier strokes were detected. Reduce jitter and sharp corrections before continuing.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.Fair">Trace quality is fair. Add a few more steady passes to make the result more reliable.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.Good">Trace quality looks good. Keep the same rhythm for a stronger result.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="AngleCalibration.Quality.Excellent">Trace quality is excellent. A few more passes can help confirm the result.</sys:String>

